<body>
<p t="81666" d="4100">An adventure is about to begin that is one of a kind
because the men behind me</p>
<p t="85766" d="2300">are the last eagle hunters in the world.</p>
<p t="88066" d="5600">Sit back and relax because you are about to embark on an adventure to discover how the concept of happiness changes</p>
<p t="93666" d="1600">at the edges of the world.</p>
<p t="99400" d="3066">My name is Giuseppe and I have a mission to travel the world</p>
<p t="102466" d="7200">to meet the most extraordinary people on the planet
and ask them a simple question: What is happiness to you?</p>
<p t="109733" d="3067">Welcome to the “Happiness Project”.</p>
<p t="116600" d="4300">In the heart of the vast
steppes of Western Mongolia live the Kazakhs,</p>
<p t="120900" d="5700">a group of legendary hunters. These nomads
are descendants of ancient tribes of Central Asia.</p>
<p t="126666" d="7234">For over 2000 years, they have perfected the art of hunting
with one of the most majestic and powerful birds of prey in the world,</p>
<p t="133966" d="1434">the golden eagles.</p>
<p t="135400" d="5000">These eagle hunters, called “berkutchi”, train the eagle chicks
from their early months of life,</p>
<p t="140400" d="3366">establishing a deep bond with their loyal companions.</p>
<p t="143766" d="5767">The eagles, trained to hunt foxes
and other small animals, become inseparable companions,</p>
<p t="149566" d="5334">capable of executing complex
hunting maneuvers under the expert guidance of their trainers.</p>
<p t="154900" d="3500">However, this ancient tradition is in danger.</p>
<p t="158400" d="5766">The berkutchi are disappearing, as the younger generation
prefers the promises of the city over eagle hunting</p>
<p t="164233" d="6500">and the reduction of natural prey caused by climate
change further threatens this practice.</p>
<p t="170766" d="4967">Batu and his son Rinat are among the last eagle hunters
of the Altai region of Mongolia</p>
<p t="175733" d="8233">they welcomed us into their family to show the world
their culture, making it immortal so it will never disappear.</p>
<p t="184033" d="5000">To become a true hunter
one must capture their own eagle with bare hands.</p>
<p t="189266" d="6500">The rite of passage that requires courage and skill.
The steep peaks of the Altai are full of dangers.</p>
<p t="195900" d="4500">The berkutchi risk their lives
to reach the nest.</p>
<p t="205266" d="3500">There is a nest up there.</p>
<p t="208766" d="14534">It is from that nest that Rinat took his chick. We climbed that peak with a rope. It is very, very dangerous!</p>
<p t="223900" d="10366">But the harder it is to reach, the more powerful the eagle will be. That&#39;s how we decide. When the eggs hatch in the spring, the best hunters capture the best eagles.</p>
<p t="235033" d="11867">And a chick taken directly from the nest can be trained more quickly, that&#39;s why we take such risks.</p>
<p t="246900" d="5766">Batu passionately tells me about the techniques they use
to create a bond with the chick from its earliest days.</p>
<p t="252766" d="6134">It must be immediately exposed to the sounds and smells of humans,
learning to recognize them as part of its new habitat.</p>
<p t="258900" d="1500">Trust is fundamental.</p>
<p t="260400" d="5500">The eagle must learn to trust its trainer
to feel safe and willing to help him hunt.</p>
<p t="265966" d="5434">For this reason, they dedicate hours
every day to feeding, caring for, and even talking to the eagle,</p>
<p t="271533" d="3633">which becomes, in all respects, part of the family.</p>
<p t="275233" d="6300">You must take care of your eagle
as you would your own child.</p>
<p t="281533" d="3533">And I see these birds as my children.</p>
<p t="285066" d="8734">My husband mainly takes care of them, but I am always happy to help when he is not around.</p>
<p t="293800" d="2500">It&#39;s nice to follow and honor our tradition.</p>
<p t="296300" d="9500">In my home village, we never had eagles, but the elders here have been training them for centuries.</p>
<p t="305800" d="8466">My husband was his grandfather’s disciple. He learned from one of the best.</p>
<p t="314266" d="4967">And now he is among the best hunters.</p>
<p t="319233" d="8333">Our children admire him a lot, especially Rinat who wants to follow in his father&#39;s footsteps and is learning about the eagles.</p>
<p t="329966" d="3934">I like the idea of having
an eagle in our house.</p>
<p t="334566" d="4100">Are you worried when your husband and son go hunting?</p>
<p t="338766" d="4800">Of course, I worry. What if they encounter some fierce animal?</p>
<p t="343566" d="9334">And if they lose their eagles? What if they get bitten
when capturing an animal? I worry a lot about my son, but then I think this is the life of a hunter.</p>
<p t="353466" d="6067">In the autumn months, the chick begins a long training process that requires patience and dedication.</p>
<p t="359533" d="5367">This process is essential to teach one of
the planet&#39;s deadliest predators to hunt</p>
<p t="364900" d="3066">and then to return trustingly to the trainer&#39;s arm.</p>
<p t="368666" d="3000">They are saddling the horses to go hunting.</p>
<p t="371666" d="3234">This is the... typical Kazakh saddle.</p>
<p t="374900" d="3766">They are very narrow, very small, and very uncomfortable,</p>
<p t="378666" d="5367">but the peculiarity of these
is that they have an armrest where</p>
<p t="384066" d="5834">the hunter can rest his arm
when holding the eagle, because the eagle weighs dozens of kilos,</p>
<p t="389966" d="1434">so he can&#39;t always hold it like this,</p>
<p t="391400" d="6200">it would be unthinkable, but it is almost invisible
because when you see him, you see him proud,</p>
<p t="397600" d="6966">with his arm extended forward, but it is resting, relaxed,
ready for action, to release the eagle into the air.</p>
<p t="404666" d="1600">Now they are... they are putting it on.</p>
<p t="417666" d="2334">Cho, cho, cho, cho.</p>
<p t="420000" d="700">We can do it.</p>
<p t="420700" d="4966">But before we start this great adventure,
I want to give you some advice on how to avoid being spied on online.</p>
<p t="426166" d="3234">If you&#39;re not using a VPN while watching this video,</p>
<p t="429400" d="5166">then your IP address, browsing history, location, and other sensitive personal data</p>
<p t="434566" d="3034">are, at best, visible to advertisers</p>
<p t="437600" d="2066">who will bombard you with ads</p>
<p t="439666" d="2100">or, unfortunately, to cybercriminals.</p>
<p t="441766" d="2834">To protect yourself, I’ve left a link below this video</p>
<p t="444600" d="3066">to try NordVPN’s new &quot;Threat Protection Pro,&quot;</p>
<p t="447666" d="4100">which allows you to protect up to 10 devices with a single subscription</p>
<p t="451766" d="3000">and make your connection and your family’s connection invisible,</p>
<p t="454766" d="4134">hiding your IP and all your personal information from malicious entities.</p>
<p t="458900" d="3366">For example, I always keep it active on my phone and PC</p>
<p t="462266" d="3300">because it not only protects all my passwords but also checks the files I download</p>
<p t="465566" d="1834">and alerts me if they contain malware.</p>
<p t="467400" d="3366">It even blocks me in time if I try to access harmful websites</p>
<p t="470766" d="3700">that could steal my data and infect my device with viruses.</p>
<p t="474466" d="3700">I recommend taking advantage of the exclusive &quot;Black Friday&quot; discount</p>
